VL  - 8
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper explores rational decision making for investment in the stock market. The first part is concerned with problems of a methodological nature, mainly dealing with the relationship between normative models and operations research. The major part explores a particular model and the various features the model possesses. The interpretation and use of a dual prices in a stochastic programming model is discussed. The final part will suggest various possible extensions into other areas.
